HEADWORD: Micturition
<hw>Mic`tu*ri"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>micturire</ets> to desire to make water, v. desid. fr.
<ets>mingere</ets>, <ets>mictum</ets>, to make water.]</ety> <def>The
act of voiding urine; urination; also, a morbidly frequent passing of
the urine, in consequence of disease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

